.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-SUMMARY 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.9.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-summary \- Analyze live Grafana dashboards through the canonical dashboard summary command.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard summary [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Analyze live Grafana dashboards through the canonical dashboard summary command.
.PP
Use this when you need the same analysis views as the local export\-tree flow, but sourced from live Grafana instead of a local export tree. Prefer dashboard summary \-\-url ... in new docs and scripts.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-page\-size
dashboard search page size.
.TP
.B \-\-concurrency
maximum parallel fetch workers.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id
analyze one explicit Grafana org.
.TP
.B \-\-all\-orgs
analyze across visible orgs.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format, \-\-output\-file, \-\-interactive, \-\-no\-header
output controls.
.TP
.B \-\-report\-columns
trim table, csv, or tree\-table query output to the selected fields. Use all for the full query\-column set.
.TP
.B \-\-list\-columns
print the supported \-\-report\-columns values and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-progress
show fetch progress.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Analyze live Grafana dashboards through the canonical dashboard summary command.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard summary --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --output-format governance
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
